OL,3,CUK increasingly exposed to health-
OL,4,Cthreatening extreme heat
OL,6,FAround the world in 2023, people were
OL,7,Fexposed to an average 50 more days of
OL,8,Fhealth-threatening temperatures than
OL,9,Fwould be expected without climate
OL,10,Fchange. Extreme drought affected 48%
OL,11,Fof global land area, the report also
OL,12,Ffound.
OL,14,FDr Marina Romanello, executive
OL,15,Fdirector of the Lancet Countdown at
OL,16,FUniversity College London, said the
OL,17,Ffindings were the most concerning in
OL,18,Fthe eight years of the report.
