OL,3,CUK increasingly exposed to health-
OL,4,Cthreatening extreme heat
OL,6,FThe higher frequency of heatwaves and
OL,7,Fdroughts around the world was linked
OL,8,Fto 151 million more people
OL,9,Fexperiencing moderate or severe food
OL,10,Finsecurity than they were each year
OL,11,Fbetween 1981 and 2010.
OL,13,FAt the same time, 61% of the world's
OL,14,Fland area saw an increase in extreme
OL,15,Frainstorms in the past decade,
OL,16,Fincreasing the risk of flooding,
OL,17,Finfectious disease and water
OL,18,Fcontamination, while the risk of
OL,19,Fmosquito-borne diseases such as dengue
OL,20,Fhas increased.
